Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @panko breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @salt{¼%tsp} and the @sweet chilli sauce{32%grams}.

> Salt for the breadcrumbs: see pantry for amount

Add the @British beef mince{240%grams}, season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray. When the wedges have 15 mins left, bake the burgers on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the burgers cook, grate the @red leicester{30%grams}. Halve the @sliced burger buns{2}.

In a medium bowl, combine the @burger sauce{30%grams} and half the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and stir to combine.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of them and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the burger buns onto another baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the remaining mayo over the bun lids.

Top the bases with the burger, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve with the chips and salad alongside and enjoy!